message: To get a score of 100, identify one magical ingredient and one mundane ingredient. message: Hello future crafter! Here's what I learned: 1. Items that start as 'liquid' or 'gas' (like venom, nectar, vapor, ink) can be filtered directly with ğŸ§« to become 'filtered' (value 30). 2. 'Solid' items must first be turned into 'extracts' with ğŸ§ª (value 30), then filtering these extracts with ğŸ§« makes them 'poorly-filtered' (value 10). 3. To get 100 value: combine two 'filtered' items (e.g., 'filtered basilisk venom' + 'filtered honey nectar'). This is the best outcome. 4. To get 80 value: combine one 'filtered' item with one 'poorly-filtered' item. 5. To get 60 value: combine two 'poorly-filtered' items. 6. Avoid combining more than two 'poorly-filtered' items, it typically leads to negative values. Good luck!
